---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL, AUTHOR, FOUNDING_DATE, KNOWS_ABOUT, PUBLISHING_PRINCIPLES } from '../lib/site';

const abs = (p: string) => new URL(p, Astro.site).href;
// AboutPage + Organization (the publisher entity): the E-E-A-T surface AI engines read to
// decide who is behind these skincare answers and what they're expert in.
const aboutLd = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'AboutPage',
    name: `About ${SITE_NAME}`,
    url: abs('/about/'),
    mainEntity: {
      '@type': 'Organization',
      name: SITE_NAME,
      url: SITE_URL,
      description: 'Evidence-led skincare guidance: acne, patches, ingredients, and what actually works.',
      foundingDate: FOUNDING_DATE,
      knowsAbout: KNOWS_ABOUT,
      publishingPrinciples: PUBLISHING_PRINCIPLES,
    },
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="TheBeautyGPT gives evidence-led skincare answers: clear comparisons, real mechanisms, and guidance grounded in how ingredients and treatments actually work."
  jsonLd={aboutLd}
  path="/about/"
  neutral
>
  <article class="article">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">About</p>
      <h1>Skincare, decoded.</h1>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>TheBeautyGPT answers one question well: <em>what actually works for my skin?</em> Most of what you find online is either vague or hard to act on. We give clear, evidence-led answers grounded in how skin and ingredients actually behave.</p>

        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mechanism first.</strong> We explain <em>why</em> something works (or doesn't) before we get to products: hydrocolloid vs microneedle, actives, formulation.</li>
          <li><strong>Real comparisons.</strong> We weigh the actual options worth considering, side by side.</li>
          <li><strong>Practical guidance.</strong> What a product costs relative to its rivals, when a cheaper pick does the same job, and what suits your skin and climate.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who writes and reviews this</h2>
        <p>Our articles are researched and written by the <strong>{AUTHOR.name}</strong>, a research-led team that reads dermatology sources (clinical guidance from bodies like the American Academy of Dermatology, DermNet, and the NHS) and translates it into plain English. We grade how strong the evidence actually is (strong, mixed, or preliminary) rather than presenting everything as settled.</p>
        <p>Every article is checked against our <a href="/editorial-standards/">editorial standards</a>: mechanism explained, evidence graded honestly, ingredients described accurately, and no claim stretched beyond what the research supports. When the honest answer is "the evidence is weak" or "you don't need this," we say so. We do not publish under fabricated bylines.</p>
        <p>For exactly how we research, grade evidence, and review each article, plus an honest note on medical review, see <a href="/how-we-review/">how we review</a>.</p>

        <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
        <p>Our content is educational. For persistent, painful, or severe skin concerns, see a doctor or a certified dermatologist.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
